<h1>API Documentation</h1>
<p>Welcome to the Zodiac API documentation! Here you can find details about available endpoints.</p>

<h2>Endpoints</h2>

<h3>Get the Zodiac Sign for the Current Date</h3>
<pre>
GET /api/v1/current_date_zodiac_sign
</pre>
<p>This method returns the zodiac sign corresponding to the current date.</p>
<p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
<pre>
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Aries",
  "start_date": "2023-03-21",
  "end_date": "2023-04-19"
}
</pre>
<p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
<pre>
404: Zodiac sign not found for the current date.
</pre>

<h3>Get the Zodiac Sign for a Specific Date</h3>
<pre>
GET /api/v1/zodiac_sign_by_date?date=YYYY-MM-DD
</pre>
<p>Use this endpoint to get the zodiac sign for a user-specified date.</p>
<p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
<pre>
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Taurus",
  "start_date": "2023-04-20",
  "end_date": "2023-05-20"
}
</pre>
<p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
<pre>
400: Invalid date format. Please use the YYYY-MM-DD format.
404: Zodiac sign not found for the specified date.
</pre>

<h3>Get the Date Range for a Zodiac Sign</h3>
<pre>
GET /api/v1/date_range_by_sign?sign=ZodiacSign
</pre>
<p>This method returns the date range for the provided zodiac sign.</p>
<p><strong>Example Response:</strong></p>
<pre>
{
  "name": "Pisces",
  "start_date": "2023-02-19",
  "end_date": "2023-03-20"
}
</pre>
<p><strong>Errors:</strong></p>
<pre>
400: The sign parameter is required.
404: Zodiac sign not found.
</pre>

